     "event_type": "zoning_amendment",
     "stage": "informational",
     "summary": "Kleinfelder consultants, introduced by DPW Assistant Engineer Mark Noonan, presented proposed zoning bylaw amendments to support Swampscott's MS4 stormwater permit compliance: parking reductions via Special Permit where transit or shared parking is nearby, green infrastructure (rain gardens, bioretention) within landscaped parking islands, and updated compact-car stall and permeable-paving standards in the Smart Growth and Glover Multifamily Overlay Districts. No formal action was taken; amendments are expected to proceed through Planning Board review before consideration at the December 2026 Town Meeting.",
